INSERT OR REPLACE INTO LocalizedText(Text, Tag, Language) VALUES
('Starts with a source of Earth and Law Mana. Also starts with a source of the Gold luxury. Khazad cities gain maluses or bonuses depending on their gold treasury per city. Overflowing Vaults of gold inspire production bonuses, happiness and even helps inspire Great People. An empty vault leads to unhappiness. Accumulate -10% less war weariness than usual.', 'LOC_SLTH_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_KHAZAD_COOL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your Cultists to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease and tsunami. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_THE_OVERLORDS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Govannon is a capable spell caster in his own right, all the more so as a hero. But his true use lies in teaching several useful adept spells to any unit once he learns them himself, including haste, dance of blades, and raise skeleton.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GOVANNON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Although not as powerful as some summons fireballs are favored by mages for their utility. They do collateral damage to stacks and can bombard city defenses. Since they fly they can strike distant targets, even those across water like nearby enemy ships. Also unlike other summons your enemies won''t gain any experience for defeating fireballs, making them perfect for wearing away at their defenses.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FIREBALL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Warriors are your earliest units and make reasonable city attackers and defenders. But beware that they will obsolete quickly. Seeks out archers for more effective defense and Axemen for more effective attacks.', 'LOC_UNIT_WARRIOR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Champions are the upgrades of Axemen and Swordsmen. Their main role remains the same, primarily conquest of enemy cities. They can upgrade into any of three or four quite different units, so consider your goal when choosing promotions for them.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CHAMPION_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The best non-limited city defender is the Longbowman. They start with a high bonus to city defense and like all archers have access to the City Garrison promotions which make them even better.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LONGBOWMAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Hell terrain is less productive than most land and the bonus types are often replaced with hell versions. For example Cows or Horses on a normal terrain type will be converted to Nightmares if the tile switches to hell terrain.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HELL_TERRAIN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('The Kuriotate Centaur Charger has two advantages over the Chariot it replaces: it requires neither the horse resource, nor the expensive siege workshop building. Their use remains the same. They have good withdrawal and high attack, providing a decent way to soften up advanced enemy units, although their defense is low so consider sending them in with some of their Centaur Archer brethren for protection.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CENTAUR_CHARGER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Horse Archer does everything the Horseman does, but better. More withdrawal chance, more strength and the addition of a first strike and first strike immune abilities make them flexible troops.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HORSE_ARCHER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Shadow spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Blur. Owning additional sources of this resource will increase the strength of any Mistforms summoned by your Archmages as well as any Shadowriders you build.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_SHADOW_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Increases the food available to the city, making it grow faster. Little care is given to the nutritional value or method of delivery of the food, however, and the health of the city is lowered by one.', 'LOC_BUILDING_ORDU_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Starts with a source of Spirit, Sun and Water Mana. Accumulate 20% less war weariness than usual. +1 [ICON_Housing] Housing in all cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_KURIOTATES_COOL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The war machine can mow down mounted units with ease, and has a good chance of withdrawal if combat goes poorly. However, it does not get defensive bonuses, so it may be wise to keep a crossbowman nearby for protected healing. Note that the War Machine automatically destroys any enemy improvements in travels over.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WAR_MACHINE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Heralds have the Herald''s Call ability. With it they grant every allied living unit in their plot the Blessed, Valor, Courage and Loyalty promotions. But the unit dies at the end of the turn. For most civilizations this would be devastating in all but the most extreme circumstances, but living units that die in the Mercurians service are reborn as Angels.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HERALD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+3 Amenities in all your cities. +3 production to all Priest Specialists. Free Blessed Ability for all Units produced in this city. New Disciple class Units trained in this city receive +14 experience. Starts a Golden Age.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_ALTAR_OF_THE_LUONNOTAR_FINAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The taskmaster will turn defeated units into slaves, which can be used as workers or added to a Balseraph city. Taskmasters also start with marksmen promotion, meaning that they will target the weakest units first.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TASKMASTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The ultimate warship, the Man-O-War comes equipped with experimental weaponry, all manner of enchanted or machined siege craft. Few lesser ships will withstand its assault, and city defenses will crumble when it starts to bombard.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MAN_O_WAR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Losha is the Calabim hero and a powerful vampire in her own right. But even beyond this she gains the Immortal promotion each time she defeats a living unit in combat, meaning she is very difficult to kill if she is kept fed.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LOSHA_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Revelers are automatically created in Sheaim cities that contain a Planar Gate and a Gambling House. Use them as scouts and despite the caecus cloth that cover their eyes, they can see very well, even detecting invisible units around them.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_REVELERS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Ravenous Werewolfs are spawned for the owner of a Werewolf unit when it kills another unit. They spawn uncontrollable in a rage, and target any opponent enemy. Once a Ravenous Werewolf kills a unit, it converts to a Blooded Werewolf and is controllable once more.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RAVENOUS_WEREWOLF_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('As with all werewolves Blooded Werewolves can also pass their lycanthropy onto living units they defeat in battle. Also each living unit they defeat gives them a small chance to upgrade yet again into the powerful Greater Werewolves.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WEREWOLVES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Use Pyre Zombies as expendable front line troops. They are as strong as Axemen, but when they are killed they explode, damaging all units (enemy and friendly) within a tile of the zombie.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PYRE_ZOMBIE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Mobius Witches have a chance of appearing in Sheaim cities with a Planar Gate and Mage Guild buildings. They have a chance of starting with a few spells.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MOBIUS_WITCH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Empyreans unique hero is Chalid Astrakein and he is a councilor, giving the player that controls him an additional vote in the Overcouncil. The Malakim hero Teutorix is also a councilor.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_OVERCOUNCIL_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Earth spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Wall of Stone. Owning this resource will give an increased chance of finding metals from mines. Owning multiple sources of this resource will increase the strength of any Earth Elementals summoned by Archmages as well as Dwarven Druids.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_EARTH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('The Bannor hero can recruit a random assortment of units. This ability is regained once he kills a demon or undead. He also has a defense increase from his unique equipment.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DONAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Freaks start mutated, giving them a wide range of random good and bad promotions. Use freaks with strong military promotions to supplement and army and sacrifice your weak freaks to create Freak Shows in your cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FREAK_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Fire Elementals grow more powerful for each Fire node you own. Players wishing to equip their archmages with these summons would do well to concentrate on fire mana, battle for additional nodes they can convert and build a tower of elements which will make all of their elementals stronger. Although Fire elementals are immune to fire damage they are notoriously ill behaved and refuse to enter frozen areas.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FIRE_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the Builder ability to construct Fishing Boats.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]+1 [ICON_Food] Food. Can only be built on valid resources.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]If built on Luxury resources, the city will gain use of that resource.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_FISHING_BOATS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Overall this means that FfH has a higher learning curve than most games, all of these options come at a cost. But once learned our hope is that there is game deep enough for players to enjoy for months or years.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WHAT_IS_FALL_FROM_HEAVEN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the Builder ability to construct a Lumber Mill.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]+1 [ICON_Production] Production. +1 [ICON_Gold] Gold if adjacent to River. Can only be built on Woods.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_LUMBERMILL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The High Priests of the Empyrean, the Luridus, have all the abilities of a Vicar as well as being able to use the [LINK=literal]Crown of Brilliance[\LINK] spell. The crown does damage to all surrounding enemies and allows the caster to see invisible units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HIGH_PRIEST_OF_THE_EMPYREAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+1 Trade Route Capacity. -10% [ICON_Gold] Gold in all Cities. 20% [ICON_Culture] Culture in all Cities. +1 Trade Route Capacity per coastal city.', 'LOC_SLTH_POLICY_FOREIGN_TRADE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A lot more than bathing goes on at a Public Bathhouse. Because of these side activities, the happiness of the city is increased, but the health is reduced.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_PUBLIC_BATHS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The sons of fire are powerful attackers, they do collateral damage to stacks they attack and can even learn to cast fire spells. They are a terror to enemy units and can decimate entire armies.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SERAPH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('They can be carried by Rangers, Hunters, and Druids. They can recon into unknown or enemy territory, expanding on their host''s already considerable recon abilities and reveal any hidden Shadows in the area.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HAWK_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Sand Lions can only be summoned by Malakim Mages, and only on desert tiles. Despite those restrictions, when they are summoned they are powerful attackers with a high movement that allow them to surprise victims.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SAND_LION_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('What can be more fearsome than a charging rhinoceros with a yelling, drinking, dwarven rider? Well, the dwarf isn''t "riding" so much as hanging on for dear life. Compared to other Knights Hornguards are slower but more powerful.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DWARVEN_HORNGUARD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Assassins attack the weakest unit in the defending stack, making them perfect for picking off enemy mages even in the best defended cities and stacks.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ASSASSIN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the Builder ability to construct Farms.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]+1 [ICON_Food] Food. Can only be built on Grassland or Plains.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Constructing farms adjacent to other Farms provides bonuses to Housing.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_FARM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Provides a free tech when built, and can be read by a unit after being picked up for a random spell effect. Some say there is a cost to using the dark tome, but many risk it for the chance at power.', 'LOC_SLTH_EQUIPMENT_INFERNAL_GRIMOIRE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Many different kind of people go into the asylum, but only one type comes out, the Lunatic. Lunatics are powerful attackers, even doing collateral damage to the stacks they attack. But their madness does cause them to run off from time to time and attack enemies with little regard to their own safety.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LUNATIC_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Hunters continue the Scout tradition of 2 movement and bonus strength against animals. They can also carry Hawks and use them to scout out areas without having to waste time or risk their lives investigating it themselves.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HUNTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Nightwatch units always start with the Council of Esus religion and can spread it without being consumed for a gold fee. They can later upgrade to Assassins or Shadow Riders. Take city garrison promotions if you expect to keep them as defensive units, or go for combat or drill for more offensive units later on.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_NIGHTWATCH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Although capable fighters on their own, Boarding parties are also able to attack naval units. And if they win, the naval unit comes under their control. They require a harbor to train and gain strength from metal resources as with other melee units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BOARDING_PARTY_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('As good as any warrior at early defense and exploration, when fed upon by a vampire using "feed" the vampire will be granted an extra movement and ability to attack again.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BLOODPET_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('High strength, high movement rate, and a decent withdrawal rate combine to form a strong utility unit. There is no best use for a Knight, it''s the fact that they can do many things so well that make them so valuable.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_KNIGHT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your priests to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease and ring of flames. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_THE_VEIL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('An Adventurer is a hero unit that can be upgraded to any of the Melee, Archer, Mounted, Recon, or Adept units the owning civilization can build. They will gain 1 experience point per turn up to 100 experience points and can quickly become powerful units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ADVENTURER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Kithra will only join Fellowship of the Leaves civilizations. Kithra is a very mobile horse archer combining a high move rate and the powerful Hero promotion.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_KITHRA_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Giant Spiders can produce Baby Spiders when killing a unit, and is invisible except next to True Sight enemies or Recon units. A capturable barbarian Animal unit that spawns in Woods, can be used to build a Spider Den that provides Silk in cities with a Carnival', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GIANT_SPIDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Starts with a source of Earth and Life Mana. They also start with a source of Iron. Accumulate -50% less war weariness than usual. +40% Bonus Production to Military Units. Mercurians are banned from producing many basic units, but the Souls of Good and Neutral can be reborn as Angels at the Mercurian gate, and upgraded into weapons of war.', 'LOC_SLTH_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_MERCURIANS_COOL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Camel Archers are identical to other civilizations Horse Archers except they don''t require horses, which are hard to find in the Malakim''s deserts.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CAMEL_ARCHER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Most believe the Immortals to be insane or undying; they are the first into battle and the last to leave. They are left to guard the cities soon to fall and sent alone deep behind enemy lines looking for exposed troops. They are not insane, and they do die, but after each death they are reborn in the capital of their civilization. A civilization can only have four Immortals at once.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_IMMORTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Radiant Guards have three advantages over axemen. They do not require a specific building, they can see invisible, and they can cast the Blinding Light spell to hold enemies in place. They do require the Empyrean state religion as well as the religion present in the city. They can upgrade into Champions or Rathas.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RADIANT_GUARD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Clan of Embers', 'LOC_CIV_CLAN_OF_EMBERS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Building this Wonder wins you the Tower of Mastery Victory. Requires the 4 preceding Towers, Tower of Elements, Tower of Divination, Tower of Alteration. Tower of Necromancy.', 'LOC_BUILDING_EIFFEL_TOWER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Monks are great for fighting demonic units. They also have the Medic promotion, making them decent healers. They don''t need a building to train so they can be created in any city.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MONK_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Being able to capture animals for the Balseraph carnivals and use the Taunt ability to cause nearby enemy units to attack their stack, Harlequin''s are useful in times of war or peace.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HARLEQUIN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Cannons are more powerful siege engines than catapults, but fill the same roles: lowering city defense bonuses and causing collateral damage. They require the gunpowder resource.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CANNON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Soldiers of Kilmorph are useful for rushing production in new cities and for early defense if a player has rushed for the Runes of Kilmorph religion before being able to produce second tier units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SOLDIER_OF_KILMORPH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+2 Amenities in all your cities. +1 production to all Priest Specialists and this city can host two more Priests. Free Blessed Ability for all Units produced in this city. New Disciple class Units trained in this city receive +8 experience.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_ALTAR_OF_THE_LUONNOTAR_CONSECRATED_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your Stonewardens to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease and shield of faith. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_KILMORPH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your Priests of Leaves to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease, summon tiger, and bloom. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_LEAVES_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Divided Souls can separate their souls from their body and allow them to wander immune to attack or notice. If the Severed Soul is in a place the Divided Soul can enter it can call the Divided Soul to it.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DIVIDED_SOUL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Eidolons are demon disciple units that offer alternate upgrades for Champions and Priests. They require Iron or Mithril and an evil alignment, but no specific building. Priest upgraded Eidolons keep their spells, and melee upgraded Eidolons keep any melee-only promotions they have acquired, so consider upgrading rather than building directly. In any case, they multi-use units with high strength and free march promotion.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_EIDOLON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+3 Amenities in all your cities. +2 production to all Priest Specialists and this city can host two more Priests. Free Blessed Ability for all Units produced in this city. New Disciple class Units trained in this city receive +12 experience.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_ALTAR_OF_THE_LUONNOTAR_EXALTED_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The apex Order Disciple ,only available by upgrading a Level 6+ , in addition to the Confessor abilities, can cast Unyielding Order, making a city Ecstatic. It requires [ICON_RESOURCE_INCENSE] Incense. Only 4 allowed in a civ at any given time.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIOR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Shadowriders are national units that must be built or upgraded in a city with the Council of Esus religion. They begin with hidden nationality, one of the few land units to do so and easily the strongest. They also have affinity for Shadow mana, gaining additional strength with every additional source gained.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SHADOWRIDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('When Equipped, gives +2 Death Combat Strength, 80% Combat Strength vs Heros, and preventing resurrection of killed units and the addition to the Mane/Angel pool.', 'LOC_SLTH_EQUIPMENT_NETHER_BLADE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Chalid is a very versatile Hero. He can cast any spells available to an Empyrean High Priest and Archmage with Sun or Law spheres, and he gains affinity from Sun Mana.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CHALID_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Hemah is an excellent spell caster available to Octopus Overlords followers only. He can take Archmage spells even though he only requires the Arcane Lore technology, giving you a head start on your rivals, and like other heroic spell casters, can take the powerful twincast promotion.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HEMAH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A Superlative mounted unit, Magnadine can also recruit mercenary units to clean up behind him as he pushes deep into enemy territory or harries an assaulting force.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MAGNADINE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('All vampires have unnaturally long life-spans, but the vampire lords have learned to cheat death itself. Whether through massive feasting or some more arcane ritual, the body of a vampire lord is recreated upon destruction. Some spend their stolen years further honing their martial prowess, but many, having experienced everything else in life, study forbidden knowledge, learning to cast advanced death and body spells without mana. A few take the final step towards immortality, and become a Lich.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_VAMPIRE_LORD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Puppets gain the spell casting abilities of their creator. Which allows casters to send their puppets into dangerous situations while remaining well away from the battle. They are also useful for casting spells that can be dangerous for the caster like Wonder or Domination.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PUPPET_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Although weak for a rank 3 summon, an Air Elemental can pass over any terrain, including water tiles, and it can see 2 tiles further than other units. Upon winning a combat, Air Elementals will summon [LINK=UNIT_LIGHTNING_ELEMENTAL]Lightning Elementals[/LINK].', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_AIR_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A powerful attacking unit that causes collateral damage to units in the opponent''s stack. Their defense is low, so they are most effective when teamed up with high defense units like archers to protect from enemy retaliation.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BERSERKER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Overlord''s special unit is the game''s earliest Undead unit. They are just as strong as Axeman but capable of traveling through coast tiles. As Undead they are also immune to disease, making them a good counter for an opponent fond of Diseased Corpse units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DROWN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Capable fighters with a handful of useful spells, vampires true strength lies in their ability to grow in power from feasting on city population-and to pass this power on to worthy allies. (s level six or higher)', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_VAMPIRE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Great Prophets can be used to build the Wonder associated with a Religion in its Holy City. It can also be used to build a tier of Altar of Luonottar.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GREAT_PROPHET_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Corlindale makes a superb mage, though if his magic can''t protect you, his diplomacy will. He can be sacrificed to make peace between your civ and all current enemies, pushing their troops outside your borders. Beware of enemy assassins, because he will be simple to eliminate should one piece your defenses.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CORLINDALE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Bearer of the Plague. Mary transmits the Plague to stacks she attacks. She is the only unit that can transmit the plague but the negative heal rate it gives will leave them vulnerable until they can reach a priest or source of sacred water.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MARY_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Tar Demons have a chance of appearing in Sheaim cities with a Planar Gate and Temple of the Veil buildings. When killed large enough tar demons will split into two smaller tar demons.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TAR_DEMON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Never one to sit back, Basium is glad to join his troops on the front line. Although powerful, a civilization that wages war with him risks his death. If Basium is lost the civilization suffers the loss of its traits.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BASIUM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('These are the wandering souls of the Divided Soul unit. They can only be created by that units Sever Soul ability. Since they are invisible they can explore the area near their Divided Soul in safety, and summon their body to them if they find something interesting.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SEVERED_SOUL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The apex Illian Disciple , only available by upgrading a Level 6+ , in addition to the Priest of Winter abilities, it can do somethine else DEBUG. It requires [ICON_RESOURCE_INCENSE] Incense. Only 4 allowed in a civ at any given time.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HIGH_PRIEST_OF_WINTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Alazkan starts with the hidden nationality and hero promotions, a potent combination for harassment of supposed allies, but most useful is his mirror ability, which summons an illusionary duplicate. Illusions cannot kill units, but are perfect for weakening any defender for Alazkan to kill without leaving him left weakened for retaliation. Both Alazkan and his mirror image will have the marksman promotion as well.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ALAZKAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Becomes a Pirate Port in 20 turns. 20% Tile Defense. +1 [ICON_Food] Food. +1 [ICON_Production] Production. +3 [ICON_Gold] Gold. Cannot be built within 2 tiles of a Pirate Cove/Pirate Harbor/Pirate Port.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_PIRATE_HARBOR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Free Morale ability applied to all units trained in this city. +10 Experience to all mounted units trained in this City.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_RIDE_OF_THE_NINE_KINGS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A Gambling House grants some happiness per 10% of the gold rate. It does tend to draw crime and increases the maintenance cost of the city. Countries that have come to depend on the happiness boost from Gambling Houses should be wary of reducing their Gold rate; doing so may start riots in their cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_GAMBLING_HOUSE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Elephants roam the wilds of Erebus. These massive behemoths are obstacles to early exploration, but will not attack. If captured they can be upgraded to units quite capable on the offense, though.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ELEPHANT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Sheaim hero is able to breathe fire, and her roar will convert any surrounding cult of the dragon units to her cause. She is also immune to magic and weaker units will often be too afraid to attack her.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ABASHI_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use the Crusader to counter your opponent''s Demonic units. Not only do they get a strength bonus against demons, but they are immune to disease, making them perfect to send into an area to eliminate any diseases the Ashen Veil and their Diseased Corpses have spread.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CRUSADER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The top fighter of the Recon line. A Beastmaster combines his own strength with those of the animals that accompany him (and a bizarre crotch biting weasel). He also converts defeated animals and the rare beast class unit. A Grove is required to train this national unit.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BEASTMASTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Treants wield the power of nature, and so start with the Woodsman promotions, being stronger and faster in Woods. However, they are vulnerable to fire.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TREANT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Don''t let the name fool you, Dragon Slayers are proficient fighters against human opponents as well, and their courage promotion takes some burden off of your spell casters.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DRAGON_SLAYER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('20% [ICON_Gold] Gold in all Cities.  Market gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Tavern gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Theatre gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.', 'LOC_SLTH_POLICY_CONSUMPTION_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Eater of Dreams can sacrifice population in cities to regain the ability to cast with his "Consume Souls" ability. This makes him a powerful defender in large cities, and able to summon multiple Balors or Fire Elementals if the city is big enough to provide him fresh victims.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_EATER_OF_DREAMS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Arthendain will only join Runes of Kilmorph civilizations. He is a healer who is able to cure disease on units in the same stack and is immune to disease himself.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ARTHENDAIN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the ability to enforce borders, and grant Open Borders to other civilizations. Also allows map trading between civilizations. (NOT_FUNCTIONAL)', 'LOC_TECH_CARTOGRAPHY_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Becomes a Pirate Harbor in 10 turns. 10% Tile Defense. +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold. Cannot be built within 2 tiles of a Pirate Cove/Pirate Harbor/Pirate Port', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_PIRATE_COVE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Fawns are terrific defenders in wooded tiles for their time, and make useful troops for players who have rushed the Fellowship of the Leaves religion before being able to build many tier two units. They can be upgraded to Satyrs later.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FAWN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('With enough experience, an adept can be upgraded to a mage, who has access to more powerful spells and is one step closer to becoming the powerful archmage. An Adept has to be at least 4th level before it can be upgraded to a Mage.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MAGE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Myconids replace Beastmasters for the Khazad. They don''t receive subdue beast or subdue animal promotions, but they can immobilize foes with their Spores spell.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MYCONID_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Pirates and Privateers are useful units for weakening rivals without declaring war. They can blockade cities, eliminating traderoutes and stealing a small amount of gold, and they can attack any ships without declaring war. Even though they have cargo space, remember that they can only carry other Hidden Nationality units, such as Council of Esus units, unless they declare nationality.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PIRATE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Flesh Golems are created with the Graft Flesh spell. Their strength can be increased by sacrificing other units to add their body parts to the Flesh Golem.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FLESH_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Upgraded bloodpets have some hope of being chosen to become vampires themselves. They also have a self-only version of the dangerous spell burning blood, which gives added move and strength, but may drive them to the barbarians.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MOROI_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('High Priests of Leaves have all the abilities of Priests of Leaves as well as being able to summon [LINK=literal]Treant[\LINK]s when they are in Forest of Ancient forest tiles.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_HIGH_PRIEST_OF_LEAVES_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('s that have attained level 6 or greater can opt to retire as a shade. These faint souls no longer engage in war or directly with the world, instead choosing to join a city to study as their profession allows. Use them to create specialists in your cities, but be careful to defend your city well. If you lose it your specialists will be gone forever.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SHADE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Elephant is the king of the early cavalry units. Granted, it is slow, but what matter, when a lumbering elephant can crush anyone foolish enough to attempt to stand their ground beneath its monstrous feet?', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WAR_ELEPHANT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Battlemasters fill the same roll as Champions from other civilizations, namely bringing force to bear on cities. They do not require buildings, however, and gain a large strength bonus on tundra.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BATTLEMASTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Rathas have three advantages over chariots. They do not require a specific building, they can see invisible, and they can cast the Blinding Light spell to hold enemies in place. They do require the Empyrean state religion as well as the religion present in the city.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RATHA_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('First to unlock this technology summons the Infernal Civilization into the game, and gives the player the option to switch to play them. (NOT_FUNCTIONAL)', 'LOC_CIVIC_INFERNAL_PACT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Battering Rams can only be created by Khazad melee units. To create a Battering Ram the unit must be in a Forest tile and use the Create Battering Ram ability.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BATTERING_RAM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The apex Veil Disciple , only available by upgrading a Level 6+ , in addition to the Ritualist abilities, can summon Balors, a strong Demonic Melee . It can also create the Hellfire Improvement, which spawns barbarian units. It requires [ICON_RESOURCE_INCENSE] Incense. Only 4 allowed in a civ at any given time.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PROFANE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Gargoyles are perfect defenders for cities, as they start with the defensive promotion, allowing for an additional 25% fortification bonus. And your foes will never walk past a cathedral or mausoleum again.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GARGOYLE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A Flurry starts with the Blitz promotion and a 2 movement rate making it an excellent way to kill separate units, or clean up a stack after an Archmage has weakened it. Because of the Blitz promotion, the Flurry becomes even more powerful as it gains Mobility promotions.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FLURRY_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('If Barnaxus has the Combat I-Combat V promotions, all golems in his empire will have a higher strength. Success of the Luchuirp is dependant on the players ability to level up Barnaxus and gain those promotions. If Barnaxus is killed his pieces will be claimed by the unit that destroyed him, a player that can recover those pieces can rebuild him in one of the Luchuirp cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BARNAXUS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Early siege engines can take the place of mages, being useful for lowering city defense bonuses and causing collateral damage to stacks. High withdrawal rates allow them to survive against even well defended stacks. They require no resources but the city must have the expensive siege workshop building.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CATAPULT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Saverous will only join Octopus Overlords civilizations. Saverous is a powerful warrior with a high strength and a built in bonus against melee troops; he frequently leads the Overlords into battle.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SAVEROUS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Caravel is a second tier scout ship, with the added ability to explore enemy territory. Its one cargo space allows you to move recon or other units to distant lands, or take the longshoreman promotion for added mobility.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CARAVEL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+25[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Snow.[NEWLINE]+10[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Tundra.[NEWLINE]-25[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Desert.[NEWLINE]', 'LOC_FROSTLING_ABILITY_TERRAINDEFENSES_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Horsemen can cover ground very swiftly, taking the fight to enemies across the realm. Few orcs have the patience or aptitude for animal training however, and the Clan of Embers fields no mounted regiments past the early wolf riders and goblin chariots. The Ogres, huge brutes with giant strides, fill the heavy cavalry niche quite effectively, slamming into enemy formations with more mass, if less speed.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_OGRE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Pit Beasts are abominations made from the pieces of various slain demons. They ache for a chance to avenge their destruction, and will heed any call to return to the mortal realm. As long as they taste blood, they can continue their assault indefinitely.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PIT_BEAST_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Summonable by Channeling units with Death III, this Undead unit starts with Fear, scattering units in combat, and Vile Touch, passing the Withered debuff to enemies in combat, weakening units, reducing experience gain, and limiting healing.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WRAITH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your Confessors to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease and Bless. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_THE_ORDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Kept alive by dark and ancient magic, Skeletons are the spirits of explorers who never found their way home, condemned to wander the frozen wastes for eternity. Though they seldom foray into the lands of the living, they will not hesitate to attack hapless wanderers of the wild.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SKELETON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Over time a lion that survives the wild will grow into a pride. A pride that ends up in terrain that will support a den will create a den that will occasionally spawn new lions that will go out to explore the world, grow into new prides and form more dens.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LION_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The apex Octopus Overlords Disciple , only available by upgrading a Level 6+ , in addition to the Cultist abilities, it can summon a Kraken. It requires [ICON_RESOURCE_INCENSE] Incense. Only 4 allowed in a civ at any given time.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SPEAKER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Ice Elementals get stronger if you have access to more types of Ice mana. They are unable to enter Desert or Burning Sands tiles but are stronger on Tundra and Snow tiles.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ICE_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Though far less dangerous than the humanoid and occasionally undead denizens of the wilderness, wild animals are nevertheless a constant hazard to those who dare venture beyond the pale.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TIGER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Great General''s can be used to draft units from a city in a pinch, or build a city a Command Post, which adds experience to units. It also buffs adjacent units combat strength.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_COMMANDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A powerful but slow unit. The summoner has to get close to unleash it on its victims, but it is a formidable city or unit attacker, and even better, the summoner can summon a new one next turn.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_EARTH_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Devouts can travel through rival territory without open borders and start with sanctify, so they are useful to keep the Armageddon counter low despite foreign wars by sanctifying city ruins. The do not have the marksman promotion, however.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DEVOUT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Any unit killed by a werewolf becomes a Ravenous Werewolf, newly born, weak and hungry. After a Ravenous Werewolf has killed a unit it becomes a Blooded Werewolf. If a Blooded Werewolf kills enough victims it can become the powerful Greater Werewolf.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WEREWOLF_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('With no resource requirement and a bonus to city defense, archers allow even the most frugal of empires to properly defend their cities. Archers have full access to the City Garrison promotions, making them even more powerful city defenders as they level.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ARCHER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Wolf Riders are fast units that are able to quickly cut into enemy lands to steal workers and cities without adequate defense. If a goblin defeats a wolf, he will automatically be upgraded to a wolf rider, often allowing Clan of Ember players to get wolf riders very early.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WOLF_RIDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+2 Amenities in all your cities. +2 production to all Priest Specialists and this city can host two more Priests. Free Blessed Ability for all Units produced in this city. New Disciple class Units trained in this city receive +10 experience.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_ALTAR_OF_THE_LUONNOTAR_DIVINE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Centaur Archer''s are great balanced units for harassing your enemies, mobile enough to cross your empire quickly and their defensive strikes make them able city defenders.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CENTAUR_ARCHER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Rathus Denmora has the same special abilities as the Sidar Ghosts: The ability to become invisible until he attacks, and the Marksman promotion for targeting the weakest unit in a stack. He does not have a low defensive strength, though, and he starts with a unique piece of equipment, the Netherblade, which gives a large bonus against other hero units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RATHUS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Ljosalfar hero is one of the earliest, allowing the elves to go on the offensive before city defense of their opponents forces them to bring along arcane units. If built after the Ljosalfar archery range, he should benefit from the +1 bonus attack strength it supplies to archers.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GILDEN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Bears that wander into a terrain that will support a bear den may settle there and form a den. Dens will occasionally spawn new bears that will wander out into the world and settle new dens.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BEAR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Formed of mithril and infused with the power of Kilmorph herself, the Mithril Golem is an avatar unit and one of the most powerful units in the game.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MITHRIL_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Ogres have tremendous regenerative ability and a very high tolerance for pain. Long lived ogres will typically be covered in scars, but these old wounds give them a thick layer of calluses, further reducing their susceptibility to pain. Their reflexes tend to be dulled somewhat, but killing a Stone-skin ogre is a tremendously difficult task. Even wounding one is rare, and is not recommended without a great withdrawal rate.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_STONESKIN_OGRE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Spectres start with the Fear promotion, meaning most living units will not attack them unless they are much more powerful than the Spectre and the can be used to scatter enemy stacks they attack.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SPECTRE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Paramanders are specific to those that have the Runes of Kilmorph state religion. They are upgrades to soldiers of Kilmorph and start with medic and demon slaying.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PARAMANDER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Triremes are the first ship able to bombard coastal cities, making them an alternate to siege engines in some environments. They start with a cargo space as well, allowing you to take escorted settlers with a skeleton crew configuration.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TRIREME_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Valkyries are immortal units and will be reborn in your capital if killed. As such they are great defenders of your units in the field, sacrificing themselves to save their allies.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_VALKYRIE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the Builder ability to construct Whaling Boats.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE] +1 [ICON_Production] Production. +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold. Can only be built on valid resources.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]If built on Luxury resources, the city will gain use of that resource.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_WHALING_BOATS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Privateers stat with Hidden Nationality, so appear as a Barbarian to other nations. In this way, its possible to weakn an unsuspecting ally or raid their trade routes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIVATEER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Reborn in the land by unknown means, Duin has been cursed with Lycanthropy: every living unit he slays becomes a Ravenous Werewolf that will follow him.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DUIN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('10% [ICON_Culture] Culture in all Cities.  Temple of Kilmorph gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Temple of Leaves gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Temple of The Order gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Temple of The Overlords gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Temple of The Veil gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.  Temple of The Empyrean gives +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity.', 'LOC_SLTH_POLICY_RELIGION_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('These fell beasts, exclusive to the [LINK=RELIGION_THE_ASHEN_VEIL]Veil[\LINK], are great at turning back the holy warriors of other religions, but beware, the Beast will consume 4 population from your cities when it is produced and your citizens will revolt for 4 turns after producing one of these in their city.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Infernal players that build Beast''s of Agares don''t suffer the population loss or the revolt in their cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BEAST_OF_AGARES_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Mistform''s start with invisibility and with hidden nationality, allowing them to sneak past other civilizations defenses and attack allied or enemy units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MISTFORM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Iron Golems are likely to form the bulk of a Luchuirp army. They have high strength but as golems will not gain promotions from combat. They aren''t going to end up as powerful as a highly promoted Champion, but losing any one particular iron golem isn''t likely to be a huge setback.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_IRON_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Satyrs require Fellowship of the Leaves religion, but no buildings, so young cities can build quickly. They can also convert any animal units without needing to attack with their mesmerize ability.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SATYR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+1 Gems resource. +1 Gold resource. Grants Enchanted Blade ability to units trained in the city.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_THE_DRAGONS_HORDE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Starts with a source of Fire and Entropy Mana.They also start with a source of Iron. Accumulate -100% less war weariness than usual. 50% [ICON_Production] Production in Capital City. The hellspawn of Infernal cities do not reproduce like the mortal rabble, but also require no sustenance, so cities are unaffected by Food. Instead, the souls of dead Evil units enter Erebus through Infernal lands as lowly Manes, who can be used to increase city Population, or be subjugated into weapons of War', 'LOC_SLTH_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_INFERNAL_COOL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Great Scientists can found an Academy in a city, increasing Science by 50%. They can also be used to contribute Science to a Technology. They can also join a city, providing Science and GPP.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GREAT_SCIENTIST_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Frydwell units are functionally identical to the Horse Archers that they replace but require deer instead of horses. They are still excellent at weakening strong units with their withdrawal chance or hitting invaders who show up in unexpected locations.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FYRDWELL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Water Elementals are capable of attacking on land or sea, and if they are defeated in combat they will split into two smaller water elementals.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WATER_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Rangers can carry hawks, and carry on a Scout''s increased movement rate. Use them to scout the map, especially to clear off barbarian units that are to strong for your hunters. Although Rangers are powerful units but they get a penalty when attacking cities. So use them to clear the unsettled lands around your enemies cities and leave city attacks to your melee units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RANGER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Rantine is a powerful early weapon against any enemies of the Clan of Embers, and a great tool against their allies, with his ability to convert barbarian cities if he is the strongest unit in it.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RANTINE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Ira are special units that are only created by the Avatar of Wrath. Although they start relatively weak, they go stronger whenever they kill an opponent.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_IRA_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+25[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Snow.[NEWLINE]+10[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Tundra.[NEWLINE]-25[ICON_Strength] Combat Strength while on Desert.[NEWLINE]', 'LOC_FROSTLING_ABILITY_TERRAINATTACKS_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Dwelling beneath the waves, the powerful krakens will only answer to the summons of the Cultists. Once they are summoned, they can travel across the seas, fulfilling their masters'' demands.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_KRAKEN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Summon Einherjar to wipe out hordes of weaker units. Their duration is increased by a turn if they defeat an opponent in combat, allowing them to remain indefinitely if they fight every turn.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_EINHERJAR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Airship allows the Kuriotates to transport units. Its especially important when they aren''t able to create any cities on a coast and they need to be able to produce transport ships from inland cities.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_AIRSHIP_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Sphener will only join the Order civilizations. Sphener and his rival Mardero are the latest and most powerful heroes in the game. Sphener has a bonus against demons and makes short work of Eidolons and Beasts of Agares.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SPHENER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Clockwork Golems are functionally identical to Berserkers, causing collateral damage to four other units when attacking stacks. They require the Machinery technology instead of Rage, however, and start with higher strength. Being golems prevents leveling up to take promotions.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CLOCKWORK_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Starting with Magic Immune gives the Nullstone Golem an obvious use of defending cities against attackers who favor direct damage spells. They will also be better than their strength would predict against any unit that relies on strength of a specific type. Golem promotion gives them additional immunities, forcing foes to take them down head on.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_NULLSTONE_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('30% Tile Defense. +20% Healing Rate. 10% Strength to allied units within 2 tiles. +2 [ICON_Food] Food. +2 [ICON_Production] Production. +4 [ICON_Gold] Gold. Cannot be built within 2 tiles of a Pirate Cove/Pirate Harbor/Pirate Port', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_FEITORIA_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Manes have a chance of being automatically created when an evil* unit dies or a neutral or evil city is razed. They are gifted to Infernal civilizations and can either be upgraded to other units or sacrificed to add population to the city.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]*Evil units are those with the Ashen Veil, Council of Esus or Octopus overlords religion. Or spellcasters that practice Death or Entropy magic.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MANES_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Council of Esus Hero, this shapeshifter can Impersonate the leader of another Civ, granting brief control of the civ. Gibbon is also an early Channeling III spellcaster.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GIBBON_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Luchuirp''s first golem unit, Wood golems are good as attackers or defenders, being stronger than the units most civs are likely to have access to at the same time. Like all golems, however, they cannot level up to gain promotions. Beware their vulnerability to fire.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WOOD_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Illusionists are similar to mages except that any creature they summon is an illusionary version of the creature. Illusions are unable to kill opponents in combat, but can reduce them almost to the point of death. This may seem like disadvantage until you consider that it leaves an opponent weakened an available to be killed by another, which can then gain experience from the battle.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ILLUSIONIST_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Centaur Lancer''s are just like knights except they don''t require access to horses to build and they have access to the Centaur specific Sprint ability.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CENTAUR_LANCER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('With the second highest Melee strength and a bonus to city attack, they were made to attack cities. Soften up the city with siege weapons, magic, or disease, then send them in.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PHALANX_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Many orcish charges have been lead by the mighty TumTum. Opposing armies, facing chants of ''TumTum, TumTum, TumTum!'' only to have a huge ogre on the back of a wild boar come bursting through the ranks at them are more likely to start laughing than be afraid. But once battle is joined TumTum is a powerful weapon for the barbarians of Erebus, and will topple unprepared empires.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_TUMTUM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Amurite longbowman is as proficient with fire magic as he is with his bow, making for a deadly defender and collateral damage attacker. Even better, it can do both at the same time, hitting nearby opponents with fireballs on its turn and being available to defend its city or stack on opponents'' turns.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_FIREBOW_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Rosier will only join the Ashen Veil civilizations. Rosier used to be a knight in the service of the Order, but has since fallen into serving the Veil. The reason for his fall is unknown.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ROSIER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Unlocks the Builder ability to construct Wineries.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE] +1 [ICON_Food] Food. +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold. Can only be built on valid resources.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]If built on Luxury resources, the city will gain use of that resource.', 'LOC_IMPROVEMENT_WINERY_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('An enormous demon of strength unmatched by mortal units, if other leaders have been making fun of you for your heresies, this ought to shut them up once and for all.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MESHABBER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Spawned for the Barbarians once the Armageddon score reaches 100, the Avatar of Wrath is very powerful, and can summon 4 Iras per turn, bloodthirsty spirits.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WRATH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Priests of Winter are only available to the Illian civilization, and are gifted when [LINK=literal]the White Hand[\LINK] ritual is completed. Use them to heal your units and they can use the special [LINK=literal]Call Blizzard[\LINK] ability.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_WINTER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('+1 Amenities in all your cities. +1 production to all Priest Specialists and this city can host one more Priests. Free Blessed Ability for all Units produced in this city. New Disciple class Units trained in this city receive +6 experience.', 'LOC_SLTH_BUILDING_ALTAR_OF_THE_LUONNOTAR_BLESSED_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Great Merchants can conduct a Trade Mission to foreign cities, earning a gold based on the distance and city size. They can also join a city, providing GPP, gold and a little food.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GREAT_MERCHANT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Brujah are functionally identical to Berserkers, causing collateral damage to four other units when attacking stacks. They also start with the vampire promotion and the abilities that come with it, as well as first level death and body spells.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BRUJAH_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Stygian Guards require a Temple to the Overlords and Copper to train. They are Immune to Disease, like all Demons, and heal faster than men, as indicated by their March promotion.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_STYGIAN_GUARD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The apex Runes of Kilmorph Disciple , only available by upgrading a Level 6+ , in addition to the Stonewarden abilities, can cast Earthquake, pillaging adjacent improvements and potentially destroying adjacent buildings. Unlike other apex Disciples, it only requires [ICON_RESOURCE_GEMS]. Only 4 allowed in a civ at any given time. (NOT_IMPLEMENTED)', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_RUNEKEEPER_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The game''s most powerful spellcaster. An archmage can learn rank 3 sorcery spells. A civilization can only have 3 Archmages at once and a Mage has to be at least 6th level before it can be upgraded to an Archmage.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ARCHMAGE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Illian Hero is an Ice Giant, who has 25% bonus in Tundra and Snow and is Immune to Cold. However, he is Vulnerable to Fire and cannot enter Desert tiles.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_WILBOMAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Say what you will about the lumbering Ogre Warchief, but they are to crafty to be trapped in battle. They will reappear in your capital if they are defeated.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_OGRE_WARCHIEF_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Druids are the only units outside of the Disciple line that have the Medic I promotion. They also have a high strength for a spell casting unit and have access to all levels of Nature magic.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_DRUID_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Mardero will only join the Ashen Veil civilizations. Mardero and his rival Sphener are the latest and most powerful heroes in the game. Mardero has a bonus against disciples and makes short work of paladins, priests, and monks.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_MARDERO_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Royal Guards require the Aristocracy civic to build, and will leave you if you change civics-so don''t bother building them if you plan to change government civics soon. They are very nice units if you meet the requirements, however, as they protect stacks against enemies with Marksman promotion and they can cast the Hope spell to add happiness and culture to a city.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_ROYAL_GUARD_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Ghosts have the same uses as assassins, starting with the marksman promotion which causes them to target weaker units first. Additionally, they can turn invisible at will, unless they have attacked this turn. This allows them to get to their target with ease, though surviving retribution may prove more challenging. They will keep this ability should they upgrade to Marksmen.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_GHOST_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Chariots require both a siege workshop and horses, but provide a unit a decent way to soften up advanced enemy units with their strong attack and withdrawal. They lack much defensive strength, though, so they need a protected place to retreat to if they are to survive retaliation.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CHARIOT_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Kuriotate Centaurs require no resource or building, and gain defensive bonuses from terrain or cities, unlike other civs'' mounted units. So in addition to the Horseman''s role of softening up strong foes with withdrawal or pillaging, they can function as mobile defenders for distant settlements. They don''t gain any added strength from being built in cities with the Nightmare resource, however.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CENTAUR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Starts with a source of Enchantment, Spirit and Water Mana. 15% Great Person Great People points generated per turn. Can recruit Great Adventurers, Heroes that gain experience per turn and can upgrade along any unit class. However, the Grigori cannot adopt any state religion, or build any religious temples.', 'LOC_SLTH_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GRIGORI_COOL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('A civilization with the Slavery civic will capture 25% of the units it defeats in combat and convert them into slave units. A slave acts like a worker, but builds at half the normal speed. Slaves can also be sacrificed to add a small amount of production to a city''s current production.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_SLAVE_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('The Luonnotar are the most powerful disciple units the Grigori have access to, though they lack priests and high priests spell abilities. They can still act as effective healers for your armies and inquisition your cities to remove religions that have spread into them.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LUONNOTAR_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Crossbowmen are the ultimate city defenders, and a well promoted one will make a city nearly impenetrable without a lengthy siege or fearsome magic-so it may prove wise to back them up with a handful of assassins or marksmen to eliminate these threats.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_CROSSBOWMAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Bone Golems are Immortal replacements that can be built directly. Being golems, their resurrection won''t save you a highly promoted unit, but will save you needing to build another.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_BONE_GOLEM_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Axemen and Swordsmen make up the first melee class warrior upgrades. They are functionally identical, gaining additional strength should their player acquire bronze, iron, or Mithril resources, and having a slight bonus to city attack. With the warfare technology, city raider promotions become available; without it your invasions may require support from siege, mounted, or arcane units.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_AXEMAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Lightning Elementals are spawned when Air Elementals win a combat. They are weak, but fast and since they start with the Blitz promotion they can attack until they are dead.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_LIGHTNING_ELEMENTAL_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Use your Vicars to speed healing, build a temple, or for their divine spells, cure disease and revelation. With promotions they can also remove unwanted religions from cities or get a chance to convert defeated foes.', 'LOC_SLTH_UNIT_PRIEST_OF_THE_EMPYREAN_DESCRIPTION', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Body spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Haste. Owning this resource will increase your units'' heal rates.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_BODY_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Fire spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Blaze. Owning additional sources of this mana will increase the strength of any Fire Elementals summoned by your Archmages.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_FIRE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Sun spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Scorch. Owning additional sources of this mana will increase the strength of any Aurelii summoned by your Archmages.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_SUN_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Nature spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Treetop Defense. Owning additional sources of this resource will increase the strength of your Druids.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_NATURE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Death spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Raise Skeleton. Owning this resource will give you a diplomacy penalty with many leaders. Owning additional sources of this resource will increase the strength of any Spectres summoned by Mages and Wraiths summoned by Archmages.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_DEATH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Chaos spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Dance of Blades. Owning this resource gives a small chance for any living unit built to start mutated.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_CHAOS_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Mind spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Inspiration. Owning this resource will give a small boost to the research of all cities.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_MIND_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Water spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Spring. Owning additional sources of this mana will increase the strength of any Water Elementals summoned by your Archmages.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_WATER_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Law spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Loyalty. Owning this resource will lower maintenance in all cities.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_LAW_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Air spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Fair Winds. Additional sources of this resource will increase the strength of Air Elementals summoned by Archmages.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_AIR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Enchantment spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Enchanted Blade. This also counts as a happiness resource.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_ENCHANTMENT_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Grants access to Entropy spells. This will allow Adepts to cast Rust. Owning this resources gives a diplomacy penalty with many leaders. It will also decrease healing of enemy units in your borders.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_MANA_ENTROPY_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: The goal of this mod is to provide a turn based strategy game with a focus on replayability. I am a huge fan of the Civilization series but after playing a dozen or so games they began to feel the same. That''s actually a pretty amazing feat, what other game can you beat a dozen times before it starts to feel the same?', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WHAT_IS_FALL_FROM_HEAVEN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('The Fool- There are three Fool cards in the deck. They allow the player to steal a card form his opponents bank and add it to the drawn card pile. If your opponent has no cards in his bank the Fool is discarded. ', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'en_US'),
('The player starts his turn by drawing a card. He can draw again or stop and collect all the cards he has turned up into his "bank". The player can continue drawing as long as he wants but his turn is ended and all of his turned up cards are discarded if he ever gets 2 cards of the same suit turned up at once. Play continues back and forth between players until all 54 cards in the deck have been drawn.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][H1]Example of Play:[\H1]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('In the end each player gets points for the highest card in his bank he has of each suit (so if he has the 3, 4 and 5 of Moons he only counts the 5) and the player with the most points wins.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][H1]Strategy:[\H1]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_8', 'en_US'),
('The player starts by turning over the 3 of Moons. He decides to draw again and draws the 6 of Wands. He decides to draw again and draws the 4 of Towers. He decides to draw again and draws the 4 of Wands. That last 4 is a duplicate, that is 2 cards of wands and all 4 cards he drew are lost and his turn is ended. If he would have stopped drawing after the 4 of Towers he would have been able to bank all 3 cards he drawn to that point and his turn would have been over.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][H1]Special Cards:[\H1]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_5', 'en_US'),
('There is global crime rate which is applied to the entire world, and each city has a random initial crime rate when it is built (which can be modified by buildings). The global crime rate is affected by some Undercouncil resolutions.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CRIME_RATE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Lairs are randomly distributed when a map is created. They spawn barbarian creatures until they are destroyed. Lairs can only be destroyed by exploring them, which may provide positive or negative results.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LAIRS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: Although the equipment system allows modders to manufacture entire arsenals of swords, shields and bows for their armies our goal with Equipment is to use it only for rare powerful artifacts with significant strategic impact. We do this to avoid micromanagement and to maintain the special allure of capturing a piece of equipment.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EQUIPMENT_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('The game takes the longbowman with drill 1 and 2 because he can do more damage (average 25 instead of average 15). The game rolls on the average 25 (0-50 weighted toward the middle) and comes up with 34 damage. The Clan of Embers Champion subtracts double his level (8) and double is defensive strength (14) so the damage is reduced from 34 to 12.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEFENSIVE_STRIKE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: Originally we designed the Kuriotates to only have their limited number of huge super cities. But being unable to expand and claim more resources was to limiting for them so we created settlements as a way to still allow the Kuriotates to expand their borders without adding to the production capacity, or significantly to their population.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SETTLEMENTS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Since the alignment attitudes are influenced by the Armageddon count (getting better towards their own alignment and worse towards the opposed alignment) when the Armageddon count gets high huge good vs evil battles tend to break out.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'en_US'),
('The only way to change your alignment is by adopting a State Religion. The Order makes any player who adopts it good, the Empyrean and the Runes of Kilmorph make evil players neutral, the Council of Esus and the Octopus Overlords make good players neutral and the Ashen Veil makes the player evil.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ALIGNMENT_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Arcane magic is quite varied. Some spells give units exclusive promotions, others create temporary units, and some enhance terrain or cities.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SPELLS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_5', 'en_US'),
('Based on a long running Dungeons and Dragons campaign Fall from Heaven is set in the dark fantasy world of Erebus. This is a world where the themes of corruption and redemption are repeated and all the characters, including the gods themselves, are imperfect.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WHAT_IS_FALL_FROM_HEAVEN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Whenever any unit attacks the game checks for any enemy unit with defensive strike in the defending stack. Only units with Blitz or haven''t attacked can make defensive strikes. Each unit that qualifies has a chance equal to his defensive strike chance to be able to make the attack. If multiple defending units can make a defensive strike only the one that does the most damage is used (so an attacking unit will only face one strike).', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEFENSIVE_STRIKE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('The chief difference between equipment and other promotions is that if a unit with a piece of equipment is killed that equipment is dropped into the tile the unit died in, rather than being lost.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EQUIPMENT_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: The AI has been adjusted to scatter the occasional Fort around, but never clump them together (this was the hardest part of setting up this system). Since we link into the terrain defense modifier system (the same system that says hills and forests grant defense bonuses) the AI does a good job of preferring to move through tiles that have "fort cover". We also tweaked the AI so that in times of war it will station units in forts to maintain the bonus.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_FORTS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('They tend to be more powerful than normal units and most have the Hero promotion, which grants them 1 experience point per turn until they reach 100 xp, allowing them to level quickly and without the risk of combat.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HEROES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Some creatures have affinity for a particular mana type. This means that they gain a strength bonus equal to their affinity amount for each source of that type of mana you control. So a creature that has Nature Affinity: 1 gets +1 for every nature mana you own. A creature with Death Affinity: 2 gets +2 strength for every death mana you control.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_AFFINITY_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: This is a doublewin mechanic. Meaning that it rewards players who are already winning, increasing the gap between winning and losing players. Although they are difficult to balance doublewin mechanics are useful because they reduce the dull grind of chewing through the players that remain in a game if the player has already won, allowing him to steamroll and achieve victory.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WEREWOLVES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('Equipment is a special object type in Fall from Heaven. It can be presented as a promotion on a unit that is carrying it, or as a non-moveable unit itself when it is sitting in a tile. Some pieces of Equipment can also be used as a building in a city.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EQUIPMENT_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Death- Drawing the death card automatically ends your turn and causes you to lose all your cards. There is only one death card in the deck.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][H1]Victory:[\H1]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_7', 'en_US'),
('Forts grow into castles and eventually citadels. The effects of each upgrade are as follows:[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Fort- gives +10% defense to anyone in the tile and +5% defense to allies within a 1 plot range[NEWLINE]Castle- gives +25% defense and +10% heal rate to anyone in the tile and a +10% defense to allies within a 2 plot range[NEWLINE]Citadel- gives +40% defense, +20% heal rate and +1 visibility to anyone in the tile and a +15% defense to allies within a 3 plot range', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_FORTS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: Functionally the AC serves to bring additional conflict to the end game. In Beyond the Sword Firaxis added espionage and corporations to address late game stagnancy. We were trying to solve the same problem but did it with the AC to try to bring conflict and a sense of urgency to the late game.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_7', 'en_US'),
('A defensive strike does an average of the unit''s Defensive Strike damage. But it is randomized and could be as little as 0 damage or twice that average. The number is modified based on the attacking unit''s defensive strength and level and the unit performing the defensive strike is marked as having attacked.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEFENSIVE_STRIKE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: The Crime Rate was created so that crime events are more likely to occur in places players would expect to see them. To make the specific situation influence the events instead of having them be purely random. It is a flavor mechanic and isn''t expected to play a strong strategic role in the game (players shouldn''t feel forced to make anti-crime buildings just to get the crime rate down).', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CRIME_RATE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('The Armageddon counter also influences the chance that fire spreads to nearby tiles and the attitude modifier between good and evil civs. There is a promotion called Stigmata that gives the unit a percentage bonus equal to half the Armageddon counter as well as other mechanics that reward some players (especially the Sheaim) for having a high Armageddon count.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_5', 'en_US'),
('This victory condition requires that the player first build the four lesser towers; the Tower of Alteration, Tower of Divination, Tower of Necromancy and the Tower of the Elements. Each of these towers require multiple mana types to be built and all the games mana types must be controlled to build all of them. Once they are all built the player can begin building the Tower of Master. If that is completed the player wins the game.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_VICTORY_TOWER_OF_MASTERY_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('The Kuriotates can only have a few real cities (the exact number depends on the map size), all the rest of their cities are settlements. Settlements are unable to produce gold, research or culture and nothing can be built in a Settlement. They don''t cost any maintenance.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Duel- 2 cities max[NEWLINE]Tiny- 2 cities max[NEWLINE]Small- 3 cities max[NEWLINE]Standard- 3 cities max[NEWLINE]Large- 4 cities max[NEWLINE]Huge- 5 cities max[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SETTLEMENTS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Although the mod isn''t a direct translation of any of the following inspiration comes from Celtic and Norse mythology, Judeo-Christian mysticism and the works of Edgar Allen Poe and H.P. Lovecraft.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WHAT_IS_FALL_FROM_HEAVEN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Crime events require a minimum Crime Rate in a city before they trigger. Certain buildings raise the crime rate, certain buildings lower the crime rate. So you are less likely to get a theft in a city with a lot of law buildings than you are in a city with a gambling house, market, smugglers'' port, etc.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CRIME_RATE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('A couple more important points-Unless your leader has the Summoner trait, summoned creatures last only one turn before they must return to the ether. Combat promotions given to spell casters apply to their spells, so a mage with combat 2 will have stronger fireball. Similarly, spell extension promotions allow a mage''s spells an extra movement point, allow him to stay a safe distance from his targets.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SPELLS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'en_US'),
('Naval units can choose one of four possible ways to crew their ships.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]1.Normal Crew- The ship retains its normal stats.[NEWLINE]2.Skeleton Crew- The ship gains +1 cargo capacity and -1 strength.[NEWLINE]3.Buccaneers- The ship gains -1 movement and +1 strength.[NEWLINE]4.Longshoremen- The ship gains +1 movement and -1 cargo capacity.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_NAVAL_CREWS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('So if hell is beginning to creep into your lands you have a few options to respond. Sending out some units to sack the Ashen Veil holy city would be an excellent way to get the Armageddon counter under control and to keep hell out of your lands. You could also gift a few powerful units to a player that is at war with the Infernals if you wanted to contribute without getting into the war directly.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'en_US'),
('There are three alignments in Fall from Heaven, Good, Neutral and Evil. Each leader starts with one and some units and civics can only be used by players of a specific alignment. It also affects your diplomatic relations with other players, granting you bonuses to players of the same alignment and negatives to players of other alignments.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ALIGNMENT_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Started with the birth of Hyborem and the Infernal civilization, hell terrain will spread as allowed by the Armageddon Counter (AC). It will always spread into Ashen Veil lands, but if the AC is over 25 it will also spread into unowned lands. If the AC is over 50 it can spread into other evil lands and if it is over 75 it can spread into neutral lands. It can never spread into the lands of good players.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HELL_TERRAIN_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Heroes are unique characters that can only appear once per game. If they are killed, they can not be rebuilt. They can be gained through a variety of means, some with certain religions, some only to certain civilizations, and some are only available to the first civilization that achieves the required tech and builds them.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HEROES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('The creation of the hero Baron Duin Halfmorn introduces the first werewolf to the world. Any living unit he creates has a chance to be raised as a newborn Ravenous Werewolf. These units are dangerous and unpredictable. If they don''t kill another unit quickly many will turn on you and become barbarian units. However, if you do manage to kill a living unit with a Ravenous Werewolf it will satiate their hunger and they will become the stronger and more loyal Blooded Werewolf.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_WEREWOLVES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('The Undercouncil serves a similar purpose to the Overcouncil. It is founded along with the Council of Esus. It can only be joined by Neutral or Evil players, and although they don''t have to worship the Council of Esus to join, they can''t be members of the Overcouncil.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_UNDERCOUNCIL_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('Somnium allows you to pick any AI leader you have contact, and aren''t at war with, and challenge them to a game of cards. If you win the game you get a positive attitude bonus with that leader, if you lose you get a negative attitude penalty.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][H1]Rules[\H1]', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('There are 10 suits with 5 cards numbered 3-7 in each. The suits are Angels, Demons, Dragons, Swords, Cups, Pentagrams, Towers, Wands, Suns and Moons. There are also 3 Fool cards and 1 Death card. ', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SOMNIUM_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('Kael''s Notes: Unique Features were added to make each map more interesting. Plus some of the wonders we have had in the mod since the beginning (like Yggdrasil and the Tomb of Sucellus) never really made much sense as buildable wonders, better to be things the player would find.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_UNIQUE_FEATURES_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('The Armageddon counter goes up when bad things happen (cities are razed, the Ashen Veil is founded, an entropy node is built, etc) and down when good things happen (Mardero dies, The Ashen Veil holy city is razed, etc.). Depending on the civs in the game the Armageddon Counter either rises slowly over the course of the game, or tends to grow to about 20-40 and then levels off (assuming the player doesn''t do anything to influence it).', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'en_US'),
('It affects many things. Hell terrain will only spread to Ashen Veil players lands until the counter hits 25, then it will start to spread to unowned tiles. At 50 it will start to spread to other evil players lands and at 75 it will start to spread to neutral lands.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ARMAGEDDON_COUNTER_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'en_US'),
('A civilization that completes the Tower of Mastery wins the game.', 'LOC_PEDIA_BUILDINGS_PAGE_BUILDING_EIFFEL_TOWER_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('[NEWLINE][COLOR_WARNING_TEXT]Reqs[COLOR_REVERT] [LINK=RELIGION_FELLOWSHIP_OF_LEAVES]Fellowship of Leaves[\\LINK] state religion', 'LOC_PEDIA_POLICYS_PAGE_SLTH_POLICY_GUARDIAN_OF_NATURE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('[NEWLINE][COLOR_WARNING_TEXT]Reqs[COLOR_REVERT] The Bannor civilization only[NEWLINE][COLOR_WARNING_TEXT]Reqs[COLOR_REVERT] Must be at War[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Blocks the building of non-military units and buildings[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Can''t start diplomacy with civilizations you are at war with', 'LOC_PEDIA_POLICYS_PAGE_SLTH_POLICY_CRUSADE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('The first available 3 movement unit is only slightly less powerful than the Axeman, while its mobility and withdrawal chance help it adapt to battles across a wide front and let it move back to safety when wounded. It is usually worth having a few Horsemen ready to respond to unexpected threats, while the rest of the army travels to the point of the attack. Horseman require a Stable and the Horse resource to be built and can be upgraded to Horse Archers and Chariots.', 'LOC_PEDIA_UNITS_PAGE_SLTH_UNIT_HORSEMAN_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Civilization Trait: Guardsman (GUA)[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]The Bannor are a good all-around civ who shine once embarking upon a total war. Their Crusade civic will give them troops on the field and decreased war weariness.', 'LOC_PEDIA_CIVS_PAGE_SLTH_CIV_BANNOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('The Avatar of Wrath is a powerful unit which is created when the Armageddon Counter gets high enough. Wrath comes into play as a barbarian unit and a large percentage of the worlds living units will convert to his cause when he appears.', 'LOC_PEDIA_UNITS_PAGE_SLTH_UNIT_WRATH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Pirate Coves are available to the Lanun.[NEWLINE]While in a cove ships gain a defensive bonus, increased healing, and a slightly better sight range.[NEWLINE]A cove can''t be built within 3 tiles of another cove. NOT YET IMPLEMENTED', 'LOC_PEDIA_IMPROVEMENTS_PAGE_IMPROVEMENT_PIRATE_COVE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('If a wild Lion is captured it can be taken to a city with a Carnival and added to the city as an attraction. This raises both the cultural and happiness effects of the Carnival.', 'LOC_PEDIA_BUILDINGS_PAGE_SLTH_BUILDING_LION_CAGE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US'),
('Fine clothes can only be produced by the Kuriotate Tailor building.', 'LOC_PEDIA_RESOURCES_PAGE_RESOURCE_FINE_CLOTHES_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'en_US');
